PLEASE HELP ME ANSWERING THIS QUESTION: What does the 'margin' property in CSS do? 

 COURSE CONTENT: Example CSS: 
 body { 
 font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
 margin: 0; 
 padding: 0; 
 } 
 The 'margin' property sets the space outside the elements.

PLEASE HELP ME ANSWERING THIS QUESTION: What is the difference between padding and margin in CSS? 

 COURSE CONTENT: Example CSS: 
 body { 
 padding: 20px; 
 margin: 0; 
 } 
 Padding adds space inside the element's border, while margin adds space outside the border.

PLEASE HELP ME ANSWERING THIS QUESTION: How do I center text using CSS? 

 COURSE CONTENT: Example CSS: 
 To center text, use the 'text-align' property with the value 'center'. Example: 
 h1 { 
 text-align: center; 
 }

PLEASE HELP ME ANSWERING THIS QUESTION: How can I apply a background color to my page using CSS? 

 COURSE CONTENT: Example CSS: 
 To apply a background color, use the 'background-color' property. Example: 
 body { 
 background-color: lightblue; 
 }

PLEASE HELP ME ANSWERING THIS QUESTION: What does the 'font-family' property do in CSS? 

 COURSE CONTENT: Example CSS: 
 body { 
 font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
 }

PLEASE HELP ME ANSWERING THIS QUESTION: How can I align elements horizontally in CSS? 

 COURSE CONTENT: Example CSS: 
 To align elements horizontally, use the 'display: flex;' property on a parent container and set 'justify-content' to the desired alignment. Example: 
 .container { 
 display: flex; 
 justify-content: center; 
 }
